msgid "Typical Physics Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:26
msgid "`world.gravity` controls global acceleration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:27
msgid "`world.damping` slows bodies over time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:28
msgid ""
"`actor.physics.simulation` chooses how an actor participates: "
"`simulated`, `manual`, `static`, or `None`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:29
msgid ""
"`actor.physics` also exposes `density`, `friction`, `elasticity`, "
"`shape_type`, and velocity helpers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:31
msgid "Collision Hooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_physics.md:33
msgid ""
"Physics worlds support dedicated actor callbacks such as "
"`on_touching_circle` and `on_separation_from_circle`. These receive the "
"other actor and contact information from the physics engine."
msgstr ""

